{
  "texts": [
    "The assembly is then re-scaffolded into highly contiguous sequences with ARCS utilizing the long-distance information contained in the linked reads.",
    "Gapfiller v1.",
    "10 [46] was used to iteratively fill gaps between contigs using paired-end reads from both the short insert Illumina libraries and the 10 × Chromium libraries.",
    "Finally, those same reads were used by Pilon v1.23 to correct base errors and local mis-assemblies.",
    "Pseudochromosome constructionChloroplast, mitochondrial, and contaminant sequences present in the meta-assembly were removed prior to construction of the nuclear pseudochromosomes."
  ]
}